@startuml 5A_Configure_Visibility
title 5-A · Configure Content Visibility & Access Rules (UC-T10, UC-T19, UC-F14, UC-F15)

start
|Tenant Admin (Owner/Admin)|
:Open content editor\n(blog post / event / media item);
:Choose visibility level;

if (Visibility selected?) then (PUBLIC)
  :Content is available to anonymous visitors and fans;
elseif (Visibility selected?) then (SUBSCRIBERS_ONLY)
  :Content requires active subscription;
else (PAID_ONLY)
  :Content requires a specific paid tier;
endif

|System|
:Validate selected visibility against tenant plan;
if (Visibility allowed?) then (No)
  :Return 403 with upgrade prompt;
  stop
else (Yes)
  :Save visibility on content record;
  :Invalidate content cache;
endif

|Anonymous Visitor / Registered Fan|
:Open content URL;

|System|
:Run VisibilityCheckDecorator;
if (Content is PUBLIC?) then (Yes)
  :Render full content;
elseif (Fan has required subscription/tier?) then (Yes)
  :Render gated content;
else (No)
  if (Required access is subscriber?) then (Yes)
    :Return preview and Subscribe to Tier prompt;
  else (No)
    :Return preview and Upgrade Subscription prompt;
  endif
  stop
endif

:Log gated content access event;
stop
@enduml
